nel app-toolbar","popover":{"title":"Lock an Operation","description":"On the Schedule tab, each operation row carries a lock icon. Click it to lock that operation — a locked operation is fixed in place, so the scheduler plans everything else around it and never moves it. Click again to unlock. Use this when an operation is already set up or promised and must not be re-timed.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".tab-bar .tab:nth-child(3)","popover":{"title":"New Work Center","description":"Switch to the Work Centers tab, then click New Work Center to define a machine or workstation. You'll set its Code, Name, Daily Capacity (Hours), Efficiency %, Number of Machines, and optional labor and burden rates. These values are exactly what the scheduler uses to compute available capacity.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".tab-bar","popover":{"title":"Work Centers Table","description":"Open the Work Centers tab to see the table: each row shows a work center's code, name, daily capacity, efficiency, machine count, active state, linked asset, and location, with Edit and Delete buttons in the Actions column. Keeping this master data accurate is what makes the schedule reflect your shop's real capacity.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".row-actions","popover":{"title":"Edit a Work Center","description":"Click the pencil (Edit) icon on any work center's row to reopen the same dialog in edit mode, pre-filled with its current values. In edit mode you also get an Active toggle — turn a center off to exclude it from scheduling without deleting it. Click Save Changes to commit, or Cancel to discard. Use Edit whenever a machine's real capacity, efficiency, or rates change.","side":"left"}},{"element":".row-actions","popover":{"title":"Delete a Work Center","description":"Click the red trash (Delete) icon to remove a work center. This does not delete instantly — a confirmation dialog opens first, naming the work center and asking you to confirm the deletion. Click Delete in the dialog to proceed or Cancel to keep it. The confirmation step protects you from accidentally removing a resource that operations are scheduled against.","side":"left"}}]}"""
